description: Latin configuratus, past participle of configurare (“to form or alter”).

verbs.description: configurate (third-person singular simple present configurates, present participle configurating, simple past and past participle configurated)

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete) To configure; to arrange or shape.
(intransitive, obsolete) To take form or position, like the parts of a complex structure; to agree with a pattern.
examples: Where Pyramids to Pyramids relate / And the whole fabrick doth configurate.
